  "text": "it follows that after TsT the horizon is still a Killing horizon that is generated by X and that the surface gravity is TsT invariant. From equation (136) it follows that the determinant of the induced metric on the spatial part of the horizon (which is a co-dimension 2 surface having V as one of its tangential directions) is preserved. Hence the horizon area is preserved under TsT (see also [CITATION_1] ).",
